

Try and create these first > 

```bash
export $(dbus-launch)
```

to the .zshrc or .bashrc file 




and the addition of 

~/.config/systemd/

~/.config/systemd/user.conf >>> 
[Manager]
DefaultEnvironment="XDG_RUNTIME_DIR=/run/user/1000" "XAUTHORITY=/home/dwarf/.Xauthority" "DBUS_SESSION_BUS_ADDRESS=unix:path=/run/user/1000/bus"



then assess the state of the service itself and allow it to relink


systemctl --failed

systemctl --user start user@1000.service ## This will return a failure on the CLI


systemctl status user@1000.service --all ## This will generally show an error


systemctl status user@1000.service --all 
> Produces output 


sudo systemctl start user@1000.service ## ACTUALLY starts the service


systemctl status user@1000.service --all ## Should be in an active state and "Ready" instead of broken.

